  "texts": [
    "Finally, condition (CH4) translates a cutoff property ensuring, like in the elastic case, that b hk ij is integrable over S 2.",
    "Unlike the elastic setting where the indistinguishability condition (EL1) alone guarantees that the collision kernels B ij have enough symmetries to link the operators Q EL ij and Q EL ji, the corresponding condition (CH1) on the chemical collision kernels B hk ij is not sufficient to pass from Q CH 1 to Q CH 3 and one needs to impose the additional micro-reversibility relation (14).",
    "Here, our goal is to characterize an explicit form of hard-potential-type kernels B hk ij that naturally satisfy condition (14) and we have done so by exploiting the symmetry properties of the pre and post-collisional relative velocities to deduce (CH3), which prescribes an explicit structure for the kinetic part.",
    "If one wanted to be less restrictive on the chemical kernels and consider more general hypotheses like (EL3') and (EL5) in the elastic framework (see our discussion in Remark 1), it would then be necessary to enforce (14).",
    "Specifically, we could replace assumption (CH3) on the kinetic part Φ hk ij (g) with the following:(CH3') There exist three constants C hk ij, C hk ij > 0 and γ hk ij ∈ [0, 1] such that C hk ij g γ hk ij ≤ Φ hk ij (g) ≤ C hk ij 1 + g, ∀v, v * ∈ R 3."
  ],
